<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Plain <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base shaft</rs> chipped on all edges (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.58</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.31</measure> x <measure precision="circa" type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.49</measure>).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div><div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>ll. 1-12, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.045-0.05</measure>; ll. 13-14, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.025</measure>. Ligatures: <foreign lang="grc">ΝΝ</foreign>, l.8.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0210" notAfter="0217" exact="both">A.D. 210-217</date>
(<rs type="criteria">reign</rs>, <rs type="criteria">nomenclature</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><w lemma="αὐτοκράτωρ">Α<unclear reason="damage">ὐ</unclear>τοκράτορα</w>  <lb n="2"/><name reg="Καῖσαρ" type="cognomen">Καίσαρα</name>  <name reg="Μᾶρκος" type="praenomen">Μᾶρ  <lb n="3" type="worddiv"/>κον</name>  <name reg="Αὐρήλιος" type="gentilicium">Αὐρήλιον</name>  <lb n="4"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <name reg="Σεουῆρος">Σεουῆρον</name>    <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="5"/><name reg="Ἀντωνεῖνος">Ἀντωνεῖνον</name><lb n="6"/><name reg="Εὐσεβής">Εὐσεβῆ</name>  <name reg="Σεβαστός">Σε<lb n="7" type="worddiv"/>βαστὸν</name>  <w lemma="βρεταννικός">Βρε<lb n="8" type="worddiv"/>τα<hi rend="ligature">νν</hi>ικὸν</w>  <w lemma="μέγας">Μέ<lb n="9" type="worddiv"/>γιστον</w></persName>  <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w>  <w lemma="δῆμος">δῆ<lb n="10" type="worddiv"/>μος</w>  <w lemma="ἐκ">ἐξ</w>  <w lemma="ἀπόλειψις">ἀπο<lb n="11" type="worddiv"/>λείψεως</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Φλάβιος">Φλα<lb n="12" type="worddiv"/>βίου</name>  <name reg="Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name>  </persName><lb n="12a"/><space unit="line" extent="1" dim="vertical"/>    <lb n="13"/><w lemma="ἐπιμελέω">ἐπιμεληθέντος</w>  <g type="stop"/>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μᾶρκος"><expan><abbr>Μάρ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">κου</supplied></expan></name>  <g type="stop"/>  <name reg="Αὐρήλιος" type="nomen"><expan><abbr>Αὐρ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ηλίου</supplied></expan></name>    <lb n="14"/>  <name reg="Χρήσιμος">Χρησίμου</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπολλωνίου</name></persName></persName></ab>
</div>


<div type="apparatus"><head>Apparatus</head><p>l. 1, first two letters damaged; <foreign lang="grc">Α</foreign> is clearly legible but <foreign lang="grc">Υ</foreign> is not.</p><p>l. 14, the final <foreign lang="grc">Υ</foreign> is tall.</p></div><div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Imperator Caesar Marcus Aurelius Severus Antoninus Pius Augustus, Britannicus Maximus. The People <supplied reason="subaudible">put up his statue</supplied> from the bequest of Flavius Attalos. Marcus Aurelius Chresimos, son of Apollonios, undertook <supplied reason="subaudible">care of the erection</supplied>.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>This text must have accompanied a statue of Caracalla, whose name included the element Britannicus from 210 A.D.</p><p> Another statue of Julia Domna (<xref type="inscription" n="1309" href="120642">12.642</xref>=MAMA 452) which is a pair to this, was found in the same area; a further statue of Caracalla (<xref type="inscription" n="1308" href="120326">12.326</xref>=MAMA 451) was set up from the same bequest.</p><p>The epimelete is not otherwise known at present.</p>
</div>
